  "texts": [
    "To investigate the formation process of diamond and graphene, MD simulations were performed for amorphous carbon under different densities.",
    "Three initial system structures with three different densities (0.5 g cc -1, 2.25 g cc -1 and 3.52 g cc -1) were generated by varying the simulation box length for a constant total number of carbon atoms of 5,000.",
    "The initial system structure was built with in-house code.",
    "First, the initial position for the first carbon atom in the simulation box was randomly selected.",
    "Then, random positions were proposed for each additional carbon atom."
  ],
